  "_comment": "Curated 'typical project' stacks fed to scripts/mine-transitives.mjs. Each entry lists the top-level packages a representative project of that shape would install. The miner resolves each via `npm install --package-lock-only --legacy-peer-deps` and scores every transitive by how many stacks pulled it in; scripts/generate.mjs then promotes high-score transitives into packages.json, displacing the lowest-popularity entries. Add a stack when a major framework lands or an existing tree changes substantially. Keep stacks lean — 4-8 top-level deps per stack is plenty, the miner walks the full transitive tree from there.",
